    • Method Detail

      • entityMode

        AnyValueWriter.EntityMode entityMode()
        Returns the wanted AnyValueWriter.EntityMode of this AnyValueWriter. A returned AnyValueWriter.EntityMode.REFERENCE signals to all entity-values that they should callback using writeNodeReference(long) or writeRelationshipReference(long) even if the whole entity is available. A returned AnyValueWriter.EntityMode.FULL signals to all entity-values that they can callback using either writeNodeReference(long), writeNode(long, TextArray, MapValue), writeRelationshipReference(long) or writeRelationship(long, long, long, TextValue, MapValue) depending on how much information is available to the value instance.
